&lt;p&gt;Design at Eve is AI-first. The workflow moves from LLM to code prototype to Figma/the tool of your choice. We want designers who already work this way, or who are ready to make it their default.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the full arc of design work. You define the problem, shape the approach, push back when the framing can be better, and stay engaged through launch and iteration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set the standard for craft and design quality on the team. Your work demonstrates what thoughtful, rigorous, AI-native product design looks like at Eve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI throughout the entire design process. From clarifying intent or surfacing edge cases early – tools like Claude are embedded at every stage.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prototype early and often. Use tools like Cursor or Claude Code to validate flows fast and partner with engineers on what moves into the product.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and scale design practices across the org. Process, shared patterns, etc., you identify solutions to new ways of working.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design for complexity without making it visible. Our users span roles across law firms. Your job is to make AI-powered, legal workflows feel simple and trustworthy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
